ns7:ScopeLimitation.ns7:ScopeLimitationWording: Limited to all steps necessary to apply for an interim order; where application is made without notice to include representation on the return date.

As to proceedings under Part IV Family Law Act 1996 limited to all steps up to and including obtaining and serving a final order and in the event of breach leading to the exercise of a power of arrest to representation on the consideration of the breach by the court (but excluding applying for a warrant of arrest, if not attached, and representation in contempt proceedings).

ns7:ScopeLimitation.ns7:ScopeLimitationWording: Limited to all steps necessary to apply for an interim order; where application is made without notice to include representation on the return date.

Limited to Family Help (Higher) and to all steps necessary to negotiate and conclude a settlement. To include the issue of proceedings and representation in those proceedings save in relation to or at a contested final hearing.
